<!-- This div contains the letter itselfs. Additions to the text are contained in <add/> elements, struck text in <hi> elements with the attribute 'strikethrough' set to true. -->
<div type="content">
<ab><expan>Gnedig<ex>er</ex></expan>
<expan>h<ex>er</ex>re</expan>, als uns ewr gnade
                            <expan>yecz<ex>unden</ex></expan>
<expan>verschr<ex>iben</ex></expan> hat von <expan>weg<ex>en</ex></expan>
                        Josse <expan>ew<ex>r</ex>s</expan> juden und Johel juden bey uns etc., das
                                <expan>hab<ex>e</ex>n</expan> wir wol
                            <expan>vernom<ex>en</ex></expan>. Nu <expan>hab<ex>e</ex>n</expan> wir
                                <expan>ew<ex>r</ex>n</expan>
<expan>gnad<ex>en</ex></expan> von <expan>ders<ex>elben</ex></expan> sache
                                <expan>weg<ex>en</ex></expan> nehst
                            <expan>verschr<ex>iben</ex></expan> und
                            <expan>geantw<ex>ur</ex>t</expan> als die
                            <expan>eingesloss<ex>en</ex></expan>
<expan>abschr<ex>ift</ex></expan> innheltt; ob <expan>ew<ex>r</ex>n</expan>
<expan>gnad<ex>en</ex></expan>
<expan>ders<ex>elb</ex></expan>
<expan>uns<ex>er</ex></expan>
<expan>br<ex>ief</ex></expan>
<expan>word<ex>en</ex></expan> sey, <expan>wiss<ex>en</ex></expan> wir niht.
                        Wie <expan>daru<ex>m</ex>b</expan> wenn der
                            <expan>vorg<ex>enante</ex></expan> Josse ewr jud
                                <expan>hiezwisch<ex>en</ex></expan>
<app>
<note><q type="date">sand Jacob tag schierist</q>25.07.1419</note>
</app> czu uns kombt, so sol er zu und von uns iiii tag geleyt
                                <expan>hab<ex>e</ex>n</expan> für uns und die
                            <expan>uns<ex>er</ex>n</expan> on geverd. Was wir im denn in seinen
                                <expan>sach<ex>e</ex>n</expan> hilfflich sein
                            <expan>süll<ex>e</ex>n</expan>, das <expan>well<ex>e</ex>n</expan> wir
                        umb <expan>ewr<ex>er</ex></expan>
<expan>gnad<ex>en</ex></expan>
<expan>will<ex>e</ex>n</expan>
<expan>g<ex>er</ex>n</expan> tun. Denn von des wandels
                            <expan>weg<ex>en</ex></expan>, als ewr gnade in
                            <expan>ew<ex>r</ex>m</expan> brief meldt, sehen wir noch
                                <expan>g<ex>er</ex>n</expan>, daz ewr gnade in einr kürcz
                                <expan>daru<ex>m</ex>b</expan> zu uns schiket, die sache <expan>zu
                                v<ex>er</ex>hörn</expan>. Hetten denn <expan>uns<ex>er</ex></expan>
                        juden icht unpillichs getan, da <expan>wölt<ex>en</ex></expan> wir zu tun,
                        daz wir hofften, ewr gnade wurd <expan>v<ex>er</ex>nemen</expan>, daz uns
                        das niht lieb <expan>w<ex>er</ex>e</expan>. Möcht
                            <expan>ab<ex>er</ex></expan> ewr gnade das umb
                            <expan>uns<ex>er</ex>n</expan>
<expan>will<ex>e</ex>n</expan>
<expan>fall<ex>e</ex>n</expan> lassen, das <expan>we<ex>re</ex></expan> uns
                        von <expan>ew<ex>r</ex>n</expan>
<expan>gnad<ex>en</ex></expan>
<expan>sunderl<ex>ich</ex></expan> zu <expan>gute<ex>m</ex></expan> dank.
                        Denn wo wir <expan>ew<ex>r</ex>n</expan>
<expan>gnad<ex>en</ex></expan> lieb etc. <expan>Dat<ex>um</ex></expan>
<expan>f<ex>er</ex>ia</expan> vi<hi rend="sup">a</hi>
<expan>p<ex>ost</ex></expan>
<expan>Pet<ex>ri</ex></expan> et Pauli.</ab>
